018/**
019 * DTO for an HTML <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/forms.html#the-meter-element">&lt;meter&gt;</a>
020 * element.
021 *
022 * <p>
023 * The meter element represents a scalar measurement within a known range, or a fractional value.
024 * It is used to display a gauge or meter showing a value within a defined range, such as disk
025 * usage, memory usage, or progress. The meter element is not suitable for representing a range
026 * of values (use the input element with type="range" for that). It is typically rendered as a
027 * visual gauge or bar that shows the current value relative to the minimum and maximum values.
028 *
029 * <h5 class='section'>Examples:</h5>
030 * <p class='bcode w800'>
031 *    <jk>import static</jk> org.apache.juneau.bean.html5.HtmlBuilder.*;
032 *
033 *    <jc>// Simple meter</jc>
034 *    Meter <jv>simple</jv> = <jsm>meter</jsm>()
035 *       .value(50)
036 *       .min(0)
037 *       .max(100);
038 *
039 *    <jc>// Meter with styling</jc>
040 *    Meter <jv>styled</jv> = <jsm>meter</jsm>()
041 *       ._class(<js>"progress-meter"</js>)
042 *       .value(75)
043 *       .min(0)
044 *       .max(100);
045 *
046 *    <jc>// Meter with complex content</jc>
047 *    Meter <jv>complex</jv> = <jsm>meter</jsm>()
048 *       .value(60)
049 *       .min(0)
050 *       .max(100)
051 *       .low(25)
052 *       .high(75)
053 *       .optimum(50);
054 *
055 *    <jc>// Meter with ID</jc>
056 *    Meter <jv>withId</jv> = <jsm>meter</jsm>()
057 *       .id(<js>"disk-usage"</js>)
058 *       .value(80)
059 *       .min(0)
060 *       .max(100);
061 *
062 *    <jc>// Meter with styling</jc>
063 *    Meter <jv>styled2</jv> = <jsm>meter</jsm>()
064 *       .style(<js>"width: 200px; height: 20px;"</js>)
065 *       .value(40)
066 *       .min(0)
067 *       .max(100);
068 *
069 *    <jc>// Meter with multiple attributes</jc>
070 *    Meter <jv>multiple</jv> = <jsm>meter</jsm>()
071 *       .value(85)
072 *       .min(0)
073 *       .max(100)
074 *       .low(20)
075 *       .high(80)
076 *       .optimum(50)
077 *       .title(<js>"Disk Usage: 85%"</js>);
078 *
079 *    // Meter with form
080 *    Meter withForm = new Meter()
081 *       .form("usage-form")
082 *       .value(30)
083 *       .min(0)
084 *       .max(100);
085 * </p>
086 *
087 * <h5 class='section'>See Also:</h5><ul>
088 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://juneau.apache.org/docs/topics/JuneauBeanHtml5">juneau-bean-html5</a>
089 * </ul>
090 */
091@Bean(typeName="meter")
092@FluentSetters
093public class Meter extends HtmlElementMixed {
094
095   /**
096    * Creates an empty {@link Meter} element.
097    */
098   public Meter() {}
099
100   /**
101    * Creates a {@link Meter} element with the specified child nodes.
102    *
103    * @param children The child nodes.
104    */
105   public Meter(Object...children) {
106      children(children);
107   }
108
109   /**
110    * <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/forms.html#attr-meter-high">high</a> attribute.
111    *
112    * <p>
113    * Low limit of high range.
114    *
115    * @param high
116    *    The new value for this attribute.
117    *    Typically a {@link Number} or {@link String}.
118    * @return This object.
119    */
120   public Meter high(Object value) {
121      attr("high", value);
122      return this;
123   }
124
125   /**
126    * <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/forms.html#attr-meter-low">low</a> attribute.

128    * <p>

130    *
131    * @param low
132    *    The new value for this attribute.
133    *    Typically a {@link Number} or {@link String}.
134    * @return This object.
135    */
136   public Meter low(Object value) {

176    * <p>
177    * Optimum value in gauge.
178    *
179    * @param optimum
180    *    The new value for this attribute.

188
189   /**
190    * <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/forms.html#attr-meter-value">value</a> attribute.
191    *
192    * <p>
193    * Current value of the element.
194    *
195    * @param value
196    *    The new value for this attribute.
197    *    Typically a {@link Number} or {@link String}.
198    * @return This object.
199    */
200   public Meter value(Object value) {
201      attr("value", value);
202      return this;
203   }
